<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_CAS_FaceBody_BodySculpting" s="315396">
  <T n="name">0xB9404332<!--String: "Body Sculpting"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_BodySculpting_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:74e3168778a85c22</T>
      <T n="text">0x47CF9E29<!--String: "A Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>body shape</font></b> can be adjusted with the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Muscle</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Fat</font></b> sliders, and then further customized by <b><font color='#199C2C'>clicking and dragging</font></b>. \n\nUse these tools to create uniquely shaped Sims!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_BodySculpting_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:74e3168778a85c21</T>
      <T n="text">0xACABED0C<!--String: "If you don't want to start from scratch, click on your Sim's body and choose the Body option from the context menu to access the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Bodies</font></b> Preset catalog. You can use these as is, or as a starting point for your sculpting."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\MuscleandFatSliders_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:72dc767e8b12f662</T>
      <T n="text">0xE0ED25B7<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Muscle</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Fat</font></b> adjustments apply to the entire Sim. Muscle controls define shape and size, while Fat controls a layer of 'soft' bulk.\n\n\nClick on your Sim's body to access the Muscle and Fat <b><font color='#199C2C'>sliders</font></b>. Click and drag the sliders to adjust them."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\BodyModifiersandPresets_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28f1f06589285100</T>
      <T n="text">0xB6CF9F7F<!--String: "You can also customize <b><font color='#199C2C'>individual body parts</font></b>! Click a body part and drag to sculpt it.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Rotate</font></b> your Sim to access even more Drag options! For example, belly size can only be modified from a side view."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
